\end_inset

obvious
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 if you do have such qualifications: it is the collection of critical points
 in dynamical systems.
 Duhh.
 Of course, what else could it have been? Nonetheless, I am excited because
 (at least for me) it offers the first practical guidepost for thinking
 about freewill in complex dynamical systems, including my current favorites:
 ecological, sociological, political, moral, biochemical, neurophysical
 and economic and geopolitical systems.
 OK, look, yeah, mathematics does not extend to these domains, but I do
 offer an explantation that is not quantum-mechanical mumbo-jumbo or that
 free will is due to the machine elves one sees during DMT trips.
 My explanation will sound like ...
 mathematical mumbo jumbo if ...
 you don't have formal training.
 But I'll try.
 The intro/apologia should be enough for most readers.
